env\&.POTUpdate(XGETTEXTFROM=\*(AqPOTFILES\&.in\*(Aq)
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp

\fIExample 4\&.\fR
You can use
\fB$XGETTEXTPATH\fR
to define the source search path\&. Assume, for example, that you have files
a\&.cpp,
b\&.cpp,
po/SConstruct,
po/POTFILES\&.in\&. Then your
POT\-related files could look like this:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
# POTFILES\&.in in \*(Aqpo/\*(Aq subdirectory
a\&.cpp
b\&.cpp
# end of file
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
